mse430 tools for experience design ms&e430 is taking on a new form this year as one of the experimental courses being created by the d school officially the hasso plattner institute of design since the d school is just starting up and is committed to pioneering innovative design techniques this year's class is at a particular moment of opportunity projects done by students in this course will help create the foundation for an empathy lab that will be a future centerpiece for the d school this is a project based studio course in which students from a variety of disciplines work together in small teams on a quarter long design project it attempts to answer the question how do you support the innovation design process in a complex world with tangible real world solutions
